# OpenSpec workflow (Experiment Hub)

## When to use what

- **OpenSpec lite** (default): **`experiment-hub-lite`** in [`openspec/config.yaml`](openspec/config.yaml) is the spike package — Human anchor, Outcomes, specs (≤5 requirements), design (Figma/breakpoints for UI), tasks §1 = user scenarios. `/opsx:propose` creates **one artifact per approval** when using lite. Strategist conversation → anchor in `proposal.md` → opsx for the rest.
- **PRD track** (optional): `@skills/prd-writer.md` can still produce `experiments/*/docs/PRD.md` for commercial narrative; lite proposal links it instead of duplicating TAM or business case.
- **OpenSpec full** (`schema: experiment-hub` in `.openspec.yaml`): Sponsor Evidence / Proceed, Visual board in proposal, multi-capability hub platform work.
- **OpenSpec vanilla**: `schema: quickstart` or upstream `spec-driven`.
- **Shared hub behavior**: Use `openspec/` for APIs, catalog, cross-experiment flows; link `proposal.md` to `PRD.md` when an experiment drives platform work.

## Git discipline

Match [github-workflow.mdc](github-workflow.mdc): one branch per logical unit (e.g. `cursor/<descriptor>`), one PR, agent does not merge. Align an active change folder name with that branch when practical.

## Figma and `design.md`

UI-impacting changes MUST document design context in `design.md` (see [figma.mdc](figma.mdc) § OpenSpec).

## Single source of truth (opsx workflow)

Edit OpenSpec agent workflow **only** under [`skills/`](../../skills/):

| Slash command   | Skill file                                                                     |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `/opsx:propose` | [`skills/openspec-propose.md`](../../skills/openspec-propose.md)               |
| `/opsx:apply`   | [`skills/openspec-apply-change.md`](../../skills/openspec-apply-change.md)     |
| `/opsx:archive` | [`skills/openspec-archive-change.md`](../../skills/openspec-archive-change.md) |
| `/opsx:explore` | [`skills/openspec-explore.md`](../../skills/openspec-explore.md)               |

`.cursor/commands/opsx-*.md` and `.claude/commands/opsx/*.md` are stubs that point here — do not duplicate steps in command files. Claude Code copies `skills/*.md` → `.claude/skills/` on session start (gitignored).

## Artifacts output (all opsx commands)

Agents MUST end responses with `## Artifacts` when they create, update, or move files under `openspec/changes/`. Build links from OpenSpec CLI JSON (`changeDir`, `outputPath`, globs, `contextFiles`, `openspec status --json`) so the rule works for every schema. Full rules: [`skills/openspec-artifacts-output.md`](../../skills/openspec-artifacts-output.md).

## Archiving

When a change is merged, move `openspec/changes/<name>/` to `openspec/changes/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-<name>/` (or use `/opsx:archive`). Canonical specs under `openspec/specs/` should already reflect the merged behavior.
